# Planned Projects

## 7. Fixed-Point DSP Library

This project will implement reusable signal-processing algorithms using fixed-point arithmetic.

The library may contain:

* Q15 arithmetic;
* Q31 arithmetic;
* saturating addition and subtraction;
* fixed-point multiplication;
* rounding and scaling;
* FIR filters;
* IIR filters;
* FFT processing;
* complex-number operations;
* magnitude and power calculations;
* automatic gain scaling.

### Q15 Representation

A floating-point value can be converted to a signed Q15 integer using:

[
x_{\text{Q15}} =
\operatorname{round}\left(x \times 2^{15}\right)
]

The approximate floating-point value is recovered using:

[
x \approx
\frac{x_{\text{Q15}}}{2^{15}}
]

### Example Saturating Addition

```c
#include <stdint.h>
#include <limits.h>

int16_t q15_add_saturate(
    int16_t left,
    int16_t right
)
{
    int32_t result =
        (int32_t)left + (int32_t)right;

    if (result > INT16_MAX)
    {
        return INT16_MAX;
    }

    if (result < INT16_MIN)
    {
        return INT16_MIN;
    }

    return (int16_t)result;
}
```

### Technical Focus

* quantization-noise analysis;
* overflow protection;
* saturation arithmetic;
* coefficient scaling;
* bit-accurate verification;
* floating-point reference comparison;
* signal-to-quantization-noise ratio;
* execution-cycle measurement;
* memory optimization;
* processor-specific optimization.

## 8. Real-Time Task Scheduler

This project will implement a lightweight scheduler for periodic and event-driven tasks.

The scheduler may support:

* periodic tasks;
* one-shot tasks;
* task priorities;
* task enable and disable operations;
* release-time tracking;
* deadline monitoring;
* missed-deadline detection;
* execution counters;
* runtime statistics;
* timer rollover handling.

### Example Task Definition

```c
typedef void (*TaskFunction)(
    void *context
);

typedef struct
{
    TaskFunction function;
    void *context;
    uint32_t period_ticks;
    uint32_t next_release_tick;
    uint32_t execution_count;
    uint8_t priority;
    uint8_t enabled;
} ScheduledTask;
```

### Technical Focus

* deterministic task dispatch;
* execution-budget monitoring;
* deadline analysis;
* timer overflow handling;
* priority management;
* scheduling jitter;
* worst-case execution-time measurement;
* testable time abstraction.

