## 11. Binary Communication Protocol Parser

This project will implement a parser for a framed binary communication protocol.

### Example Frame

```text
+------------+--------+------+---------+----------+
| Start Byte | Length | Type | Payload | CRC      |
+------------+--------+------+---------+----------+
```

The parser will accept one byte at a time and retain its internal state between calls.

### Parser States

* waiting for synchronization;
* reading the header;
* validating the length;
* receiving the payload;
* reading the CRC;
* validating the frame;
* recovering from malformed input.

### Technical Focus

* streaming byte processing;
* partial-frame handling;
* malformed-frame recovery;
* CRC validation;
* resynchronization;
* buffer-boundary protection;
* protocol version handling;
* fuzz testing;
* hostile-input validation.

