* callback functions;
* state machines;
* communication protocols;
* sensor-data processing;
* DSP implementation;
* fixed-point arithmetic;
* multithreading;
* synchronization;
* atomic operations;
* lock-free design;
* deterministic memory allocation;
* hardware abstraction;
* fault management;
* software testing;
* static analysis;
* dynamic analysis;
* performance profiling;
* CMake;
* Make;
* Git;
* continuous integration.

# Relevance to Engineering Roles

The projects are relevant to positions such as:

* Wireless DSP Firmware Engineer;
* Embedded Software Engineer;
* Firmware Engineer;
* PHY Firmware Engineer;
* DSP Software Engineer;
* Real-Time Software Engineer;
* Systems Software Engineer;
* Communication Software Engineer;
* Baseband Software Engineer;
* Embedded Linux Software Engineer;
* Test and Verification Engineer.

The project collection demonstrates C programming for applications that process data, interact with hardware, operate under resource constraints, and require reliable runtime behaviour.

